                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 836/44.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Grisoom</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Petropolis</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-01-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 2, 1907</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Griscom states that the continuance of our 20 per cent preferential tariff
                    reduction was authorized by the Congress which expired December 30, and that the
                    preferential continues as before, except that linotypes and cash registers are
                    added under the classification of typewriters.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
